# DNOTAM (Digital NOTAM) - Service Specification

## Important Clarification

> **CORRECTION (January 2026)**: This document was updated to correct an error regarding ED-254.
> 
> **ED-254 (EUROCAE) is specifically for Extended AMAN (Arrival Sequence Service), NOT for DNOTAM.**
> 
> For DNOTAM, there is **no formal service standard/specification** like ED-254. Instead, DNOTAM uses:
> 1. **Service Definition** published on the SWIM Registry
> 2. **SWIM-TI Yellow Profile** (EUROCONTROL SPEC-170) for protocol requirements

## DNOTAM Service Definition

**Official Source**: SWIM Registry

**URL**: https://eur-registry.swim.aero/services/eurocontrol-digital-notam-subscription-and-request-service-010000

**What the Service Definition provides**:
- Service description and scope
- Subscription interface specification
- Request interface specification (WFS GetFeature)
- Payload schema requirements
- Operational parameters

**Protocol requirements come from**: EUROCONTROL SPEC-170 (Yellow Profile)
- AMQP 1.0 over TLS 1.2/1.3 for Publish/Subscribe
- REST/HTTP over TLS 1.2/1.3 for Request/Reply
- mTLS authentication requirements
- Security and audit requirements

## DNOTAM Overview

**Digital NOTAM (DNOTAM)** is the digital replacement of traditional text-based NOTAMs (Notice to Airmen). It provides system-readable, validated aeronautical information about operational changes affecting flight operations.

**Data Model**: AIXM 5.1.1 + Event Schema

## Current NOTAM vs Digital NOTAM

### Current NOTAM Limitations

**Example**: `A1926/21 NOTAMN`
```
Q) EHAA/QMRLC/IV/NBO/A/000/999/5218N00446E005
A) EHAM
B) 2109060500
C) 2109150500
E) RWY 09/27 CLSD
```

**Problems**:
- ❌ Only human readable (personalized item E)
- ❌ Space for errors
- ❌ No visual representation
- ❌ Hard to read and understand
- ❌ Difficult to keep overview
- ❌ No machine validation

### Digital NOTAM Benefits

- ✅ **System readable**: Machine-parseable structured data
- ✅ **Data validation**: Automated validation against schemas
- ✅ **Traceable associations**: Linked to related aeronautical features
- ✅ **Export capability**: Can be exported as Digital NOTAM dataset
- ✅ **AIXM-based**: Uses standardized Aeronautical Information Exchange Model
- ✅ **Visual representation**: Can be displayed on maps/charts

## Supported DNOTAM Event Types

### Mandatory Event Scenarios

1. **Runway Closure (RWY.CLS)**
   - Temporary or permanent closure of runways
   - Affects take-off and landing operations

2. **Taxiway Closure (TWY.CLS)**
   - Closure of taxiways affecting ground movement
   - Impacts taxi routes and airport capacity

3. **Stand Status**
   - Aircraft stand availability changes
   - Parking position status updates

4. **Obstacle New (OBS.NEW)**
   - New obstacles affecting flight operations
   - Temporary or permanent obstructions

5. **Navaid Unserviceable (NAV.UNS)**
   - Navigation aid equipment failures
   - VOR, DME, ILS, NDB unavailability

6. **ATS Airspace Activation (SAA.ACT)**
   - Activation/deactivation of airspace
   - Restricted areas, danger zones, military areas

## Mandatory Use Cases

### Required for IFR Airports

1. **ePIB (Electronic Pre-flight Information Bulletin)**
   - Status: **REQUIRED**
   - Scope: All IFR airports
   - Purpose: Provide digital briefing information

2. **Take-off Landing**
   - Status: **REQUIRED**
   - Scope: All IFR airports
   - Purpose: Runway and approach information

3. **Runway Contamination (SFC.CON)**
   - Status: **REQUIRED**
   - Scope: All IFR airports
   - Purpose: Surface condition reporting

4. **Airspace Status VFR**
   - Status: **REQUIRED**
   - Purpose: VFR airspace availability

### Recommended

- **ePIB for CP1 Airports**: Recommended but not mandatory

## Service Interfaces (from Yellow Profile)

**Note**: Interface requirements are defined by EUROCONTROL SPEC-170 (Yellow Profile), which applies to ALL SWIM services including DNOTAM.

### Subscription Interface (REST/HTTP)

**Protocol**: REST/HTTP over TLS 1.2/1.3

**Endpoints** (as per SWIM Registry Service Definition):
- `POST /swim/v1/subscriptions` - Create subscription
- `GET /swim/v1/subscriptions/{id}` - Get subscription details
- `PUT /swim/v1/subscriptions/{id}` - Update subscription (ACTIVE/PAUSED)
- `DELETE /swim/v1/subscriptions/{id}` - Delete subscription
- `GET /swim/v1/topics` - List available topics

### Request Interface (WFS)

**Protocol**: REST/HTTP over TLS 1.2/1.3

**Endpoints**:
- `GET /swim/v1/features` - WFS GetFeature for AIXM data

### Event Streaming Interface (AMQP)

**Protocol**: AMQP 1.0 over TLS 1.2/1.3

**Operations**:
- Subscribe to topics
- Receive real-time DNOTAM event notifications
- Queue management

**Reference**: EUROCONTROL SPEC-170 (Yellow Profile)

## CP1 (Common Project 1) Requirements

### Stakeholder Roles

#### AISP (Aeronautical Information Service Provider)

**Requirements**:
- **DNOT-102**: Provide DNOTAM service
- **DNOT-105**: Ensure data quality and validation
- **DNOT-106** (optional): Extended data scope

**Responsibilities**:
- Publish DNOTAM events
- Maintain baseline aeronautical information (AIFS)
- Ensure data consistency with AMAP

#### ANSP (Air Navigation Service Provider)

**Requirements**:
- **DNOT-103**: Consume DNOTAM service
- **DNOT-104** (optional): Extended consumption

**Responsibilities**:
- Subscribe to relevant DNOTAM topics
- Integrate DNOTAM into ATM systems
- Minimum 1 use case implementation

#### EAD (European AIS Database)

**Role**: Central repository and distribution point

### Compliance Requirements

**Minimum Compliance**:
- At least **1 use case** implemented
- System consuming and using DNOTAM data
- Integration with existing ATM systems

**EASA Interpretation**:
> "A full replacement of current NOTAM concept"

## Data Scope and Relationships

### AIFS (Aeronautical Information Flight Service)

DNOTAM events are expressed in relation to **static aeronautical information baseline** provided by AIFS.

**Required AIFS Data Scope** (to support DNOTAM):

| Feature | Requirement | Scope |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| AIFS-101-1 | Required | Basic aerodrome data |
| AIFS-101-2 | Required | Runway/taxiway data |
| AIFS-101-3 | Required | 18 CP1 Airports |
| AIFS-101-4 | Recommended | All IFR Airports |
| AIFS-101-5 | Optional | Extended features |

**Mandatory Data Elements**:
- `AeronauticalGround`
- `AircraftStand`
- `Light`
- `AirportHeliport`

### AMAP (Aerodrome Mapping)

**Requirements**:
- **AMAP-101**: CP1 Airports (required)
- **AMAP-102**: IFR Airports (optional)
- **AMAP-103**: AISP provision
- **AMAP-104**: ANSP consumption
- **AMAP-105**: AO (Airport Operator) provision (optional)

**Data Scope**:
- **Temporality**: Current and Next AIRAC cycle
- **Geographical Scope**: CP1 Mandated airports
- **Usage**: Enabling ePIB (optionally)

**Note**: No consumption mandated for AMAP (unlike DNOTAM)

## Integration with ASM (Airspace Management)

### Regulatory Context

**ICAO Requirement**:
> "A NOTAM shall be originated and issued concerning information which is of a temporary nature or not sufficiently known in advance"

**Challenge**: If NOTAM not issued, how is General Aviation informed?

### Digital NOTAM and ASM SWIM Service Link

- DNOTAM events can be triggered by ASM changes
- Airspace activation/deactivation generates DNOTAM
- Integration between ASM SWIM service and DNOTAM service required

**Current Limitation**:
- LARA V5 does not support DNOTAM integration

## Technical Implementation

### Service Definition Structure

**Components** (per SWIM Registry Service Definition):
1. **Service Description Document**
   - Interface definitions
   - Payload schemas
   - Operation specifications

2. **Information Definition**
   - Event scenarios table
   - Data model mappings
   - AIXM feature associations

3. **Interface Specifications**
   - Subscription API
   - Request API (WFS GetFeature)
   - AMQP messaging

### Payload Schemas

**Format**: XML based on AIXM 5.1.1

**Event Structure**:
```xml
<Event>
  <eventType>RunwayClosure</eventType>
  <featureReference>
    <AIXM:RunwayDirection gml:id="RWY_09_EHAM"/>
  </featureReference>
  <validTime>
    <beginPosition>2021-09-06T05:00:00Z</beginPosition>
    <endPosition>2021-09-15T05:00:00Z</endPosition>
  </validTime>
  <scenario>CLSD</scenario>
</Event>
```

**Key Elements**:
- `eventType`: Type of DNOTAM event
- `featureReference`: Link to AIFS baseline feature
- `validTime`: Event validity period
- `scenario`: Specific scenario code

### Security Requirements

**PKI (Public Key Infrastructure)**:
- EACP (European Aviation Common PKI) certificates
- mTLS for service-to-service communication
- Certificate-based authentication

**Cyber Security**:
- Information Security Management System (ISMS)
- Coverage of Digital Certificate usage
- Monitor, Detect, Analyze, Respond, Recover capabilities

## Deployment Considerations

### Harmonization Requirements

**CP1 System Requirements**:
- Harmonized SWIM Specifications
- SWIM-TI Yellow Profile compliance (EUROCONTROL SPEC-170)
- SWIM Registry Service Definition conformance

**Status**: Not all specifications published yet (as of documentation date)

### ATM Systems Impact

**CP1 Mandate**:
> "ATM systems = All systems using AIM information"

**Implication**: All systems consuming aeronautical information must be capable of using DNOTAM

### Migration Strategy

**Transition Period**:
- Parallel operation of traditional NOTAM and DNOTAM
- Gradual phase-out of text-based NOTAM
- Full replacement as per EASA interpretation

**Stakeholder Responsibilities**:
- Country-level compliance responsibility
- Stakeholders mandated but implementation is national

## DNOTAM Implementation (RHOne Context)

### Architecture Components

1. **DNOTAM Provider**
   - Publishes DNOTAM events to AMQP topics
   - Exposes Subscription Manager REST API
   - Validates events against AIXM 5.1.1 schemas

2. **DNOTAM Consumer**
   - Subscribes to DNOTAM AMQP topics
   - Processes events and updates local systems
   - Persists events for audit

3. **Integration Layer**
   - AIFS baseline integration
   - AMAP data correlation
   - Event-to-feature association

### Technology Stack (Red Hat)

- **Integration**: Quarkus with swim-framework (swim-framework-consumer / swim-framework-provider)
- **Broker**: ActiveMQ Artemis (AMQP 1.0)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL/MongoDB (event persistence)
- **Platform**: Red Hat OpenShift
- **Security**: Kubernetes Secrets (EACP certificates)

### Deployment Pattern

**Helm Chart** with conditional components:
- `mode: provider` - DNOTAM Publisher only
- `mode: consumer` - DNOTAM Subscriber only
- `mode: both` - Full bidirectional capability

**Kubernetes Operator**:
- Single Custom Resource (CR) deployment
- Automated lifecycle management
- Complexity abstraction for ANSPs

